article.headline: Oral Roberts 73, FIU 65
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Michael Craion had 19 points and eight rebounds and Oral Roberts beat Florida International 73-65 on Tuesday night. Jake Lliteras made all four of his 3-point attempts to score 12 points for the Golden Eagles (4-2), who were playing in the NIT Season Tip-Off tournament. Dominique Morrison added 13 points for Oral Roberts. Phil Taylor led Florida International (1-3) with 22 points. DeJuan Wright added 17 points while Dominique Ferguson had 10 points and a game-high nine rebounds for the Panthers.
